pattern.base.htmlview.PatternWebBrowser is not part of Eclipse.
This might indicate something wrong in the SWT Variant class though.

This is a valid exception thrown from Variant (and described in the javadoc 
for getInt).  If the Variant is of type VT_EMPTY and you ask for the integer 
value, you will get this exception.

I recommend you either handle the exception or check the Variant type 
(Varinat.getType == VT_I4) before calling getInt.

BTW WebBrowser returns VT_EMPTY when it is successful and VT_I4 when it fails 
with an error value.
